<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,764,1439]" pageId="10" pageNumber="353">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,451,800,827]" pageId="10" pageNumber="353">Original description:</emphasis>
“rigonfio, varici mutiche. La varietà qui notata è riferita al 
<taxonomicName authority=", Michelotti" authorityName="Michelotti" box="[1123,1433,800,827]" class="Gastropoda" family="Muricidae" genus="Murex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="10" pageNumber="353" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="conglobatus">
<emphasis box="[1123,1298,800,826]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="353">M. conglobatus</emphasis>
, Michelotti
</taxonomicName>
, il cui tipo è fossile del terziario piemontese; la nostra forma mediterranea, pur essendo vicinissima a quella descritta dal geologo torinese, ne differisce perché alquanto meno rigonfia e raccorciata ed è quindi da distinguersi col nome di 
<emphasis box="[180,370,908,934]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="353">propeconglobata</emphasis>
, la quale velerebbe così ad essere l’anello di congiunzione principale tra le forme di questo tipo viventi e quelle esistenti un tempo nel mare pliocenico” [bulgy, with rounded varices. The— 
<taxonomicName authority="(Linneus, 1758)" authorityName="Linneus" authorityYear="1758" baseAuthorityName="Linneus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" class="Gastropoda" family="Muricidae" genus="Hexaplex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="10" pageNumber="353" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="trunculus">
<emphasis box="[1216,1436,944,970]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="353">Hexaplex trunculus</emphasis>
(Linneus, 1758)
</taxonomicName>
, reported as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[470,811,980,1007]" class="Gastropoda" family="Muricidae" genus="Murex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="10" pageNumber="353" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="trunculus" subGenus="Muricantha">
<emphasis box="[470,542,981,1006]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="353">Murex</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[558,690,980,1006]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="353">Muricantha</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[705,811,980,1006]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="353">trunculus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L.— 
<taxonomicName box="[867,1001,980,1006]" pageId="10" pageNumber="353" rank="variety" variety="here">variety here</taxonomicName>
described is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority=", Michelotti" authorityName="Michelotti" class="Gastropoda" family="Muricidae" genus="Murex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="10" pageNumber="353" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="conglobatus">
<emphasis box="[1256,1429,980,1006]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="353">M. conglobatus</emphasis>
, Michelotti
</taxonomicName>
, whose 
<typeStatus box="[360,408,1017,1043]" pageId="10" pageNumber="353">type</typeStatus>
is a fossil from the Piedmontese Tertiary; our Mediterranean form, despite being very close to that described by the Turinese geologist, differs in being less swollen and shortened, and therefore deserves the name 
<emphasis box="[219,409,1088,1114]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="353">propeconglobata</emphasis>
; it constitutes the conjunction between living forms and Pliocenic fossils].
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,764,1439]" pageId="10" pageNumber="353">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,435,1124,1151]" pageId="10" pageNumber="353">Material examined:</emphasis>
a single shell, presumably fossil, labelled by Monterosato “ 
<taxonomicName authority="Bell-Boll. Della Soc. Dei Naturalisti di Napoli 1901, p. 99" authorityName="Bell-Boll. Della Soc. Dei Naturalisti di Napoli" authorityYear="1901" class="Gastropoda" family="Muricidae" genus="Murex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="10" pageNumber="353" phylum="Mollusca" rank="variety" species="trunculus" variety="propeconglobata">
<emphasis box="[1109,1252,1124,1150]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="353">M. trunculus</emphasis>
v. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="353">propeconglobata</emphasis>
Bell—Boll. Della Soc. Dei Naturalisti di Napoli 1901, p. 99
</taxonomicName>
—Sciacca—Coll.Adami—fossile?” [Sciacca—Adami collection—fossil?] (MCZR-M-7623) actually belongs to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Linneus, 1758)" authorityName="Linneus" authorityYear="1758" baseAuthorityName="Linneus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[848,1250,1196,1223]" class="Gastropoda" family="Muricidae" genus="Hexaplex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="10" pageNumber="353" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="trunculus">
<emphasis box="[848,1065,1196,1222]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="353">Hexaplex trunculus</emphasis>
(Linneus, 1758)
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1265,1386,1196,1223]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1460,1485]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,395,1432]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1436,414,1432]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 4. A–C. Bittium iadertinum var. coralligena. A. Original figures. B. Possible type material from Capri Island (Naples)—4.9×1.5 mm. C. Original label handwritten by Bellini. MCZR—not numbered. D, E. Murex trunculus var. propeconglobata. D. Fossil(?) shell from Sciacca (Agrigento)—72.4×52.8 mm. E. Original label handwritten by Monterosato. MCZR- M-7623. F, G. Fusus (Pseudofusus) pulchellus var. curta. F. Original figures. G. Shells from Capri Island (Naples) and original label handwritten by Monterosato (up to 16 mm in total height). MCCIC—drawer 8, n. 146. H. Clathromangilia granum var. prausi. Original figures. I. Left. Cardium (Parvicardium) exiguum var. minimum. Original figure. I. Right. Cardium (Parvicardium) exiguum var. paludosum. Original figures." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3449572" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3449572/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="353">Fig. 4D, E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="353" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,764,1439]" pageId="10" pageNumber="353">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,1233,1259]" pageId="10" pageNumber="353">Remarks:</emphasis>
having been instituted on the basis of insignificant morphological characteristics, we rank it infrasubspecific, and thus not available (
<bibRefCitation author="ICZN &amp; International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature" box="[588,724,1269,1295]" pageId="10" pageNumber="353" refId="ref17437" refString="ICZN [International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature] (2012) International code of zoological nomenclature. 4 th Edition. International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London. Available from: http: // www. iczn. org / (accessed 15 Feburary 2019)" type="url" year="2012">ICZN 2012</bibRefCitation>
: Art. 
<date box="[787,884,1268,1295]" pageId="10" pageNumber="353" value="1945-10-02">10.2, 45</date>
.5, 45.6, glossary). Despite this, it was listed as a variety of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Linneus, 1758)" authorityName="Linneus" authorityYear="1758" baseAuthorityName="Linneus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[264,666,1304,1331]" class="Gastropoda" family="Muricidae" genus="Hexaplex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="10" pageNumber="353" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="trunculus">
<emphasis box="[264,482,1304,1330]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="353">Hexaplex trunculus</emphasis>
(Linneus, 1758)
</taxonomicName>
by several subsequent authors (
<bibRefCitation author="Dollfus, G. - F." box="[1018,1169,1304,1330]" pageId="10" pageNumber="353" pagination="86 - 124" refId="ref16952" refString="Dollfus, G. - F. (1926) Description des mollusques des couches du Pliocene inferieur de Kopliku, pres Scutari, d'Albanie. Journal de Conchyliologie, 70, 86 - 124." type="journal article" year="1926">Dollfus 1926</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Priolo, O." box="[1180,1313,1304,1330]" pageId="10" pageNumber="353" pagination="501 - 576" refId="ref18834" refString="Priolo, O. (1964) Nuova revisione delle Conchiglie marine di Sicilia - Memoria XV. Atti dell'Accademia Gioenia di Scienze Naturali, 6 (16), 501 - 576." type="journal article" year="1964">Priolo 1964</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Settepassi, F." pageId="10" pageNumber="353" refId="ref19264" refString="Settepassi, F. (1970) Atlante Malacologico dei Molluschi marini viventi nel Mediterraneo. I. Corporazioni Arti Grafiche, Roma, 296 pp." type="book" year="1970">Settepassi 1970</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Sabelli, B. &amp; Giannuzzi-Savelli, R. &amp; Bedulli, D." box="[223,434,1340,1367]" pageId="10" pageNumber="353" refId="ref18986" refString="Sabelli, B., Giannuzzi-Savelli, R. &amp; Bedulli, D. (1992) Catalogo Annotato dei Molluschi Marini del Mediterraneo. Vol. 2. Libreria Naturalistica Bolognese, Bologna, 498 pp." type="book" year="1992">
Sabelli 
<emphasis box="[309,367,1340,1366]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="353">et al.</emphasis>
1992
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Houart, R." box="[447,593,1341,1367]" pageId="10" pageNumber="353" refId="ref17369" refString="Houart, R. (2001) A review of the recent Mediterranean and Northeastern Atlantic species of Muricidae. Evolver, Roma, 227 pp." type="book" year="2001">Houart 2001</bibRefCitation>
). This taxon was not figured by 
<bibRefCitation author="Bellini, R." box="[963,1138,1340,1367]" pageId="10" pageNumber="353" pagination="85 - 121" refId="ref15636" refString="Bellini, R. (1902 a) Contribuzione alla conoscenza della fauna dei molluschi marini dell'isola di Capri. Bollettino della Societa dei Naturalisti in Napoli, Series 1, 15, 85 - 121." type="journal article" year="1902">Bellini (1902a)</bibRefCitation>
; however, shell characters highlighted in the original description clearly point to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linneus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[756,896,1376,1402]" class="Gastropoda" family="Muricidae" genus="Hexaplex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="10" pageNumber="353" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="trunculus">
<emphasis box="[756,896,1376,1402]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="353">H. trunculus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The nominal taxon may comprise a complex of cryptic species (
<bibRefCitation author="Marzouk, Z. &amp; Aurelle, D. &amp; Said, K. &amp; Chenuil, A." box="[331,565,1412,1439]" pageId="10" pageNumber="353" pagination="411 - 428" refId="ref17794" refString="Marzouk, Z., Aurelle, D., Said, K. &amp; Chenuil, A. (2017) Cryptic lineages and high population genetic structure in the exploited marine snail Hexaplex trunculus (Gastropoda: Muricidae). Biological Journal of the Linnean Society, 122 (2), 411 - 428. https: // doi. org / 10.1093 / biolinnean / blx 070" type="journal article" year="2017">
Marzouk 
<emphasis box="[441,497,1412,1438]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="353">et al.</emphasis>
2017
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
